2026-05-03T23:23:32.2496966Z               "id": "da7c568c2c4ccdb59121cc4d6be7e952fb2aa63f",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2502601Z               "message": "Add EnableDirectDns toggle and inherit unset client options from server config\n\nAdds a server-wide kill switch for checks that bypass the configured\nrecursive resolver to talk directly to authoritative nameservers or\npublic resolvers (8.8.8.8 / 1.1.1.1 / 9.9.9.9): DNS propagation, lame\ndelegation, SOA serial consistency, NS glue records, parent delegation,\nopen recursive resolver detection, and AXFR-based DKIM selector\ndiscovery. When EnableDirectDns is false, those checks return Info\n\"skipped\" instead of grinding through 45-second DNS timeouts in\nenvironments where outbound raw UDP/53 to internet IPs is blocked but a\nlocal forwarder is permitted.\n\nThe toggle plumbs through AppConfig (env var / config.json / Config UI),\nValidationOptions (per-request body and ?noDirectDns=true), the\n/api/defaults response, and AND-merges in both validation endpoints so\nclients cannot re-enable a category disabled by the admin.\n\nAlso fixes a UI bug: the validator page checkboxes ignored the\nserver-side default and always rendered checked for new sessions even\nwhen the corresponding option (e.g. EnableSmtpProbes) was disabled in\nconfig.json. loadUserOptions now records which keys were actually\npopulated from localStorage, and the /api/defaults handler applies\nserver defaults to any key the user has not explicitly saved.",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2507269Z               "timestamp": "2026-05-01T03:41:32Z",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2507583Z               "tree_id": "e00003e46fc6e89ddbf16b2d6b141e539d79afd9",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2508066Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/da7c568c2c4ccdb59121cc4d6be7e952fb2aa63f"
