2026-05-03T23:23:32.2521003Z               "id": "2d446475df03bf7bc79fbf69c95bfbdcab643fa7",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2529229Z               "message": "Per-request structured logging with parallel-safe trace plumbing\n\nThree concerns were tangled:\n1. Singletons (DnsResolverService / SmtpProbeService / HttpProbeService /\n   ProbeCache) exposed Trace as a single Action<string> field. Two parallel\n   validations setting it would clobber each other; request A's DNS traces\n   could end up routed to request B's logger.\n2. Trace messages emitted per-validation lacked any way to identify which\n   request, user, domain, phase, or check produced them.\n3. Logs were always Simple-format text — no structured output for log\n   aggregators.\n\nFix:\n- New TraceContext (AsyncLocal Sink/Phase/Check). All five Trace properties\n  on the singletons now read/write TraceContext.Sink, so concurrent flows\n  see independent sinks via AsyncLocal copy-on-Task.Run semantics.\n- DomainValidator updates TraceContext.Phase and TraceContext.Check around\n  each phase/check entry/exit, including the fire-and-forget HTTP prefetch\n  spawns (now tagged Phase=PREFETCH).\n- Web Program.cs:\n  - JSON console formatter by default in Production, Simple in Development.\n    Logging:Console:FormatterName overrides either default.\n  - Request-scope middleware sets RequestId/Method/Path on every line.\n  - Auth middleware adds Username (or \"(anonymous)\" / \"(auth-disabled)\")\n    and IsAdmin once the user is resolved.\n  - Both validation endpoints (POST async + GET sync) wrap their work in\n    a job scope with JobId/Endpoint/Domain and a per-trace-message scope\n    with Phase/Check. JobId, Username, RequestId stay raw — they're\n    identifiers, not PII; Domain is masked when MaskTrace=true (default).\n\ndocs/configuration.md describes the log format selection, the structured\nfields available, and example jq queries for filtering by JobId, Phase,\nor Username.\n\nVerified with parallel POST /api/validate against two domains:\n1006 traced log lines split cleanly 430/576 between the two jobs, each\njob's scope carried only its own (masked) domain — no cross-contamination\nacross the 87 distinct check names captured.",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2535997Z               "timestamp": "2026-05-01T04:18:57Z",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2536311Z               "tree_id": "4360a5a8e4050c88eca35f1523b3ea5ed98a7e39",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2536786Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/2d446475df03bf7bc79fbf69c95bfbdcab643fa7"
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2537194Z             },
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2537377Z             {
