2026-05-03T23:23:32.2552231Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2552573Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2552791Z               },
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2552969Z               "distinct": false,
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2553235Z               "id": "12b0332771d011911180a8e195d0e1f8c3b6b07f",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2556315Z               "message": "Domain combo: substring filter + merge known/dkim with selectors as label\n\nThree changes:\n- Filter as you type: each keystroke re-renders the dropdown, keeping only\n  rows whose domain or any of its DKIM selectors substring-match the\n  input. Open-on-type so closing with Escape and resuming typing reopens\n  it (matches typical autocomplete UX).\n- Substring (contains), not prefix — so \"abc\" matches \"wwwabc.com\" and\n  \"selabc1\" alike.\n- Merged the previous \"Known domains\" and \"Per-domain DKIM\" groups into\n  one \"Known / DKIM\" group. The Recent group still appears separately.\n- Source label per row: when DKIM selectors are configured for the\n  domain, those selectors are shown (comma-joined) in place of the old\n  \"dkim\" / \"known\" tag. Domains with no selectors render no tag.",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2558771Z               "timestamp": "2026-05-01T06:27:42Z",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2559092Z               "tree_id": "eea7acd21711fe38d70cac9c2dd132251680d08a",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2559542Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/12b0332771d011911180a8e195d0e1f8c3b6b07f"
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2559933Z             },
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2560102Z             {
