2026-05-03T23:23:32.2562959Z               "id": "8e9834885fe96d76ee1ce4751a56a7adb287887f",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2566147Z               "message": "Run docker build/push in parallel with slow integration tests\n\nSplit the previous build-and-test job into two:\n  build       — restore + compile + unit tests (fast)\n  integration — CLI smoke tests against external domains (slow)\n\ndocker now depends only on build, so it kicks off as soon as the unit\ntests pass instead of waiting on the multi-minute integration suite.\npush-build-logs depends on all three (build, integration, docker) so the\nlog summary still captures everything; the result is now derived from\nall three jobs and the per-job statuses are surfaced individually in\nbuild-summary.md.\n\nA failing integration run no longer blocks the docker push — it shows up\nas a fail row in the summary and the test artifacts. If integration\ngating is wanted in future, add 'integration' back to docker's needs.",
