2026-05-03T23:23:32.2596575Z               "distinct": false,
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2596845Z               "id": "ac6cd584d6313bdb75f16ecb0d57ae3083d5516c",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2603247Z               "message": "Make config defaults overridable + add /api/debug/proxy\n\nPOST /api/validate previously AND-merged the request body's enable*\nflags with the live config snapshot, so a client could only opt OUT of\nadmin-enabled categories — never opt IN to one the admin had disabled.\nThat meant the new EnableDoh per-validation checkbox couldn't actually\nturn DoH on if the server-side default was false (the common case).\n\nDrop the AND-merge entirely. The admin config still seeds the validator\nUI defaults via /api/defaults — new sessions inherit them, the JSON tab\nsaves them, etc. — but each request's options block is authoritative.\nPer-domain DKIM and the global DKIM list still fall back to config when\nthe request hasn't supplied any (existing logic).\n\nAdds GET /api/debug/proxy?url=... (admin-only): reports what\nHttpClient.DefaultProxy.GetProxy resolves for the target URL, whether\nNO_PROXY would bypass, and the proxy-related env vars actually visible\nto the running process (HTTPS_PROXY / HTTP_PROXY / ALL_PROXY / NO_PROXY,\npreferring uppercase, falling back to lowercase). Built for diagnosing\n\"(HTTP 0)\" failures from the BIMI / MTA-STS / security.txt / crt.sh\nchecks — the response distinguishes \"vars not seen by the process\",\n\"NO_PROXY suffix-matching the host\", and \"DefaultProxy returned no\nproxy\". Env-var names are emitted via a Dictionary so the JSON\nserializer's camelCase policy doesn't mangle them (HTTPS_PROXY would\notherwise become httpS_PROXY).\n\ndocs/configuration.md updated: the four enable* rows now read \"default,\nrequest body wins\" rather than \"kill switch / AND-logic\", and a new\n\"Diagnosing proxy issues\" subsection demonstrates the endpoint.",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2608687Z               "timestamp": "2026-05-01T07:43:34Z",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2609009Z               "tree_id": "296cbd6aed63d2512af9d498c8458ebdb4ef645b",
