2026-05-03T23:23:32.2620763Z               "id": "452328744e996509dee10cfde7deb5dd1bb69807",
2026-05-03T23:23:32.2623444Z               "message": "DoH: send Accept: application/dns-json header\n\nCloudflare's /dns-query defaults to the binary application/dns-message\nformat and only returns JSON when the Accept header explicitly requests\nit; the ?ct=application/dns-json query-param shortcut is unreliable in\npractice. That left Cloudflare reported as \"(unreachable): A=[] MX=[]\"\neven on networks where the endpoint was perfectly reachable.\n\nAdds GetWithAcceptAsync to HttpProbeService (separate cache key per\nAccept value) and switches DohQueryAsync to use it for both Google and\nCloudflare endpoints — Google accepts the header too, so a single path\ncovers both.",
